  <title>
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">Emergency response to conflict-affected communities in central Kachin</narrative>
  </title>
  <description type="1">
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">CA will implement the response through local partner, Metta, who is well placed strategically and programmatically to respond, having led the JST assessments and with access to project locations. Activities outlined are: 
&#x2022;	Food assistance for 3,000 individuals (600 households) for two months, prioritising women, children and people with disability. Food package per person per month: 13.5 kg rice; 1 litre oil; 1.8 kg pulses; 0.15 kg salt, in line with WFP standards. 
&#x2022;	Temporary shelters (tarpaulins and bamboo poles) for 100 households (500 individuals).
&#x2022;	NFIs for 450 newly displaced households (2,250 individuals), including kitchen utensils (pot, spoon/plate, kettle, cup, frying pan, trivet) bedding (plastic mats, blanket, mosquito nets, mattress, pillow), clothing and hygiene items (including women&#x2019;s sanitary items) as needed.</narrative>
  </description>
  <description type="2">
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">The project aims to provide life-saving support to communities affected by conflict. The intervention is expected to provide urgent food, non-food item and shelter needs of community, as well as leverage for the partner to raise more funds to support more communities in need.</narrative>
  </description>
